<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79293a9a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s689p"><num value="689p">§ 689p.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator may issue such regulations as it deems necessary to carry out the provisions of this part in accordance with its purposes.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79293a9b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/699/tIII/s367">Pub. L. 85–699, title III, § 367</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/8/s1/b/3">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(8) [§ 1(b)(3)]</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–664.)</sourceCredit>
